enhanced_by.reason: The generateInvalid method provides invalid SSN patterns that are used to validate the generated SSN in generateValid.
The countryCode method provides the country context for which the SSN is being generated, which is relevant for setting up the environment.
Both generateValid methods produce valid SSNs, and the assertions for the simpler generateValid can be informed by the more complex one that includes additional parameters.
The getValidSsn method is deprecated but functionally similar to generateValid, making it a good reference for assertions.
